description:
CLASS (user screenshots, runs 5-6 2026-07-03): the engine renders the portrait model while its textures/materials still stream, and those REAL frames pass every pipeline gate (bundle-provenance color, keyed mask, tear<=10):
(1) green face + saturated-orange crown (material placeholder colors) -- displayed on a run where src[color bundle=*/scan=0] (refutes the wrong-buffer/scan theory; the content is IN the bundle RT);
(2) white untextured skull + noise-speckled mushroom growths (mid-stream mips) -- displayed then STUCK (window 9 slot7 Locked-up Bean: clean=29 then checker-classified frames ate the rest, no publishes -> static garbage);
(3) dark mottled closeup blob (window 10/11); NOTE the extreme-closeup framing in several (model fills ~93% of frame; share pass_min=7).
RELATED: the 'torn' storms (windows with constant tear=39-40, e.g. run-6 window 7 slot5 Patches torn=171 clean=29 -> static correct head, user 'no animation') are plausibly NOT GPU tearing but the tear metric scoring the CONTENT's own hard edges (crown/hair) -- torn frames and placeholder frames co-occur; needs a discriminator (temporal stability of high-step rows = content; random rows = tearing).
FIX DIRECTION (no compromises): a RAM material/texture-residency semaphore -- RE the ModelIns/material streaming state so the publish gate holds until the model's textures are resident (the same signal the engine uses to swap placeholder materials out). Color-band classifiers do NOT generalize (class includes white/brown/dark frames). Also revisit portrait_looks_like_checker (it silently ate 266 real frames in window 9 -- now counted per-window as checker=).
